<br>
You spend virtually everyday of your life with the same person for three years.  Suddenly, that person stops talking to you.  Won't return phone calls.  Seems annoyed when you catch them at home.<br>
<br>
It really begins to bother you, so you point blank ask them what you did wrong.  They tell you that you did nothing.  HOWEVER, something has changed and that they do not know what, but whatever it is, it's unchangeable.  They no longer wish to talk to you.<br>
<br>
Turns out, at the same time the person stopped talking to you, they also 'coincidentally' began dating someone else.  Heavily.<br>
<br>
You have never felt so betrayed, lied to and hopeless in your entire life.  The one person that could comfort you wants nothing to do with you.  Because that person - the one you can't imagine living without - is very much in love with someone else, when just a day prior to the disowning - they professed their undying love.<br>
<br>
It's a disgusting feeling and it feels like part of you died.<br>
<br>
Do you wish them luck, pat them on the back, tell them it's okay and that you understand.  -- <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>That's what I did, and now that the sorrow is beginning to settle in, I'm beginning to feel very angry.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Or do you tell them what a cruel, conniving, heartless, deceitful cretin you think they are?<br>
<br>
Do you even have the right to be angry?  Technically? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kuladen>kuladen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I was a mod<br>for an hour<br>and all I got<br>
