<br>
Why reduce myself, yes?  Or perhaps I should rant on them, so they can roll their eyes and walk away.<br>
<br>
But I am angry nonetheless, and I wasn't sure if I was over-reacting or how you could love someone and feel this anger towards them at the same time.<br>
<br>
And I am a 'one love' type of person.  To me, this is more painful than the death of my parent.  It's hard to move on and anticipate a life without them in it, when you don't understand the reason or have the desire to suddenly stop caring about them and in this same chapter, you swore you would love them forever.<br>
<br>
